                     <hi rend="largeCaps">THOMAS TINDALL</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18470816-1924-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18470816-1924-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18470816-1924-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="embezzlement"></interp> for embezzlement.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470816-name-1062" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1062" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1062" type="surname" value="HEDGE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1062" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>CHARLES HEDGE.</persName>
                  </hi> I am a coal-merchant, at Eaton-wharf, Pimlico. The</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184708160188"></xptr>
               <p>prisoner was my servant—it was his duty to receive money—the money brought to the wharf it was his duty to pay to me each night—if he received 2<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>., and 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. on the 27th of July, he has not paid it to me—he ought to have paid them both.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. ROBINSON.</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> He was in the habit of receiving large sums? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No, not large sums—5<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. or 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. a day—he may have in<lb></lb>tended to pay me these sums, but I do not know where the money was to come from—he gave me no account of them.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470816-name-1063" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1063" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1063" type="surname" value="CHIGNELL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1063" type="given" value="ANN"></interp>ANN CHIGNELL.</persName>
                  </hi> I had coals of the prosecutor—on the 27th of July I paid the carman (Gilder) 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—this is the receipt.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470816-name-1064" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1064" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1064" type="surname" value="GILDER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1064" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN GILDER.</persName>
                  </hi> I am the carman—I received the money from Mrs. Chignell; I gave it to the prisoner, who is the clerk.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Do you recollect giving him that 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—I have received a little money from time to time—I received this money for Mr. Coomb—these were not Mr. Hedges' coals at all.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470816-name-1065" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1065" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1065" type="surname" value="BURTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1065" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM BURTON.</persName>
                  </hi> I paid 2<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. about the 24th of July to the prisoner for Mr. Hedge.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. ROBINSON</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">to</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. HEDGE.</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Have you any partner? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No—Mr. Coomb does his business at the wharf, and sends out coals—it was the duty of the prisoner to receive this money and hand it to me—I am answer<lb></lb>able for it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT.</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> You directed the prisoner, your servant, to receive it? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—it was his duty to pay the money received of Mrs. Chignell to Mr. Coomb—the 2<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. paid by Mr. Burton to the prisoner was my money.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
